At the [[2010 United States census|2010 census]], there were 2,039 people and an estimated 671 households and 359 families residing in Yanceyville.<ref name="Census 2010"/> In 2010, the estimated median age was 41.1 years. For every 100 females, there were an estimated 110.2 males.<ref name="ACS">{{Cite web|title=American Community Survey|url= https://data.census.gov/table?g=1600000US3776000&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S0101|access-date=December 25, 2022|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

===2000 census===
At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]],<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vbBNAQAAMAAJ&dq=yanceyville+2000+census+data&pg=RA1-PA8 |title=2000 Census of Population and Housing: Population and Housing Unit Counts |date=2003 |publisher=U.S. Department of Commerce, Economics and Statistics Administration, U.S. Census Bureau |language=en}}</ref><ref name="GR2" /> 
there were 2,091 people and an estimated 658 households and 400 families residing in Yanceyville. The population density was {{convert|450.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 748 housing units at an average density of {{convert|161.3|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 53.99% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 44.29% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1.00% [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]], 0.33% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.14% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.33% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.91% from two or more races.

Out of the 658 households, 29.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 33.0% were married couples living together, 24.3% had a female householder with no husband present, and 39.2% were non-families. 36.8% of all households consisted of individuals living alone and 19.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.21 and the average family size was 2.88.

The age distribution of the town's population consisted of 19.6% under the age of 18, 8.4% from 18 to 24, 32.9% from 25 to 44, 20.8% from 45 to 64, and 18.3% who were 65 years of age or older.

The [[median income]] for a household in Yanceyville was $20,353 and the median income for a family was $26,417. Males had a median income of $24,632 versus $20,398 for females. The per capita income for the town was $16,956. About 23.3% of families and 27.7% of the population were below the poverty line, including 41.7% of those under age 18 and 24.1% of those age 65 and over.

